{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: composition-eu-eps_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a FSH Composition instance conforming to the CompositionEuEps
    profile (HL7 Europe Patient Summary). This is the document-level resource
    that aggregates all clinical sections and entries of an EPS bundle into
    a single structured composition. It is the most architecturally significant
    template in the EPS pipeline — every clinical resource generated by the
    other templates is referenced from within one of this template's sections.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: CompositionEuEps
    Fixed elements:
      type.coding  = $loinc#60591-5 "Patient summary Document"
      status       = #final
      title        = "European Patient Summary"
      confidentiality = #N

  `patientdisplay` — INLINE SET WITHIN THE FSH HEADER
    A Twig `{% set %}` statement appears between FSH header keyword lines:
      Title: "HL7 Europe Patient Summary (EPS) Composition"
      {% set patientdisplay = patient.name ~ " (" ~ patient.age ~ " y/o) - synthetic data" %}
      Description: "Complete … for {{ patientdisplay }}"
    This is valid because Twig processes the entire template before FSH sees
    it — the `{% set %}` is stripped and `patientdisplay` is resolved inline.
    `patient.age` is a field not present on the clinical resource templates;
    it is a pre-computed display string (e.g. "45") supplied by the PHP caller.

  COMPOSITION DATE FORMAT — ESCAPED DATETIME
    `composition.date|date('Y-m-d\\TH:i:s\\Z')` produces an ISO 8601 UTC
    datetime string such as `2025-09-14T12:00:00Z`. The double-backslash pairs
    in the Twig source are necessary to produce literal `T` and `Z` in the
    output:
      Twig source    : `'Y-m-d\\\\TH:i:s\\\\Z'`
      Twig string    : `Y-m-d\\TH:i:s\\Z`
      PHP date() out : `2025-09-14T12:00:00Z`
    PHP's date() treats `\X` as "literal character X", so `\T` → `T` and
    `\Z` → `Z`. The four backslashes in the Twig source encode two Twig-level
    escaped backslashes, each becoming one PHP-level escape.

  SECTIONS LOOP — KEY-VALUE DICT ITERATION
    `sections` is an associative array (PHP dict / Twig mapping) where each
    key is a named FSH slice identifier and each value is a section object.
    The Twig key-value loop form is used:
      {% for slicename, section in sections %}
    This makes `slicename` available as the named section slice for FSH:
      * section[{{ slicename }}]
    In this EPS template, the slice name is always used directly — unnamed
    sections (`section[+]`) are not supported here (unlike HDR).

  SECTION OBJECT STRUCTURE
    Each value in the `sections` dict carries these fields:
    ┌───────────────────────────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ Field                         │ Type     │ Description                                  │
    ├───────────────────────────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ title                         │ string   │ Human-readable section title.                │
    │ code                          │ string   │ Full FSH code expression: "system#code"      │
    │                               │          │ (already formatted; not system/code/display  │
    │                               │          │ separately).                                 │
    │ display                       │ string   │ Display text for the code.                   │
    │ text                          │ string   │ Pre-built XHTML string for section.text.div. │
    │                               │          │ Must be used with \| raw to avoid escaping.  │
    │ indicateEmptyListReason       │ string?  │ When "TRUE", emits emptyReason instead of    │
    │                               │          │ entries. Mutually exclusive with entries.    │
    │ entries                       │ object[] │ Array of entry objects (see below).          │
    └───────────────────────────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  ENTRY OBJECT STRUCTURE (one element of `section.entries`)
    ┌───────────────────────────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ Field                         │ Type     │ Description                                  │
    ├───────────────────────────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ id                            │ string   │ UUID of the referenced resource.             │
    │ sectionentryslicename         │ string?  │ Optional named entry slice. When non-empty,  │
    │                               │          │ wrapped in `[]` and prepended to `[+]`:      │
    │                               │          │ `* entry[slicename][+] = Reference(…)`       │
    │                               │          │ When empty, plain `* entry[+] = Reference(…)`│
    │ nosectionentry                │ string?  │ When "TRUE", this entry is suppressed        │
    │                               │          │ entirely — no FSH entry rule is emitted.     │
    │                               │          │ Used when a resource is included in the      │
    │                               │          │ bundle but not referenced in this section.   │
    └───────────────────────────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  ENTRY SLICE NAME ASSEMBLY
    The entry slice name is conditionally wrapped in brackets and prepended to
    the mandatory `[+]` append operator:
      {% if entry.sectionentryslicename is empty %}
      {% set sectionentryslicename = "" %}
      {% else %}
      {% set sectionentryslicename = "[" ~ entry.sectionentryslicename ~ "]" %}
      {% endif %}
      * entry{{ sectionentryslicename }}[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ entry.id }})
    Result when empty  : `* entry[+] = Reference(…)`
    Result when "foo"  : `* entry[foo][+] = Reference(…)`

  EMPTY SECTION REASON
    When `section.indicateEmptyListReason == "TRUE"`, `emptyReason` is emitted
    instead of the entries loop:
      * emptyReason = $list-empty-reason#nilknown
    This signals that the section is intentionally empty (e.g. "no known
    allergies") rather than simply having no data. The condition is an explicit
    string comparison ("TRUE"), not a boolean — the caller must pass exactly
    the string "TRUE".

  sectioncount VARIABLE
    `sectioncount` is incremented once per section but its value is never
    used in the FSH output. It is available as a debugging / inspection aid
    after rendering but produces no template output.

  COMPOSITION NARRATIVE — #empty, PLACED AFTER SECTIONS
    The Composition's own `text.div` (distinct from each section's text) is
    set to `#empty` at the very end of the FSH body, after all sections.
    This ordering means the `text.*` rules come last in the compiled FSH.
    The section-level text.div values are #generated (each section carries its
    own pre-built XHTML narrative).

  NO HTML TABLE
    No `addHTML_td*()` or `addHEAD_th()` calls are made. %%HEAD%% is empty.
    %%HTML%% calls `emitHTML() | raw` for structural completeness but the HTML
    bag is never populated, so the output is an empty string.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                         │ Type     │ Description                                    │
  ├──────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ composition.instanceid           │ string   │ UUID for the Composition resource.             │
  │ composition.identifier           │ string   │ Business identifier value.                     │
  │ composition.date                 │ date     │ Document date; filtered to ISO 8601 UTC.       │
  │ patient.instanceid               │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.                  │
  │ patient.name                     │ string   │ Full display name.                             │
  │ patient.age                      │ string   │ Pre-computed age string (e.g. "45") for the    │
  │                                  │          │ Description display only.                      │
  │ provider.instancerole            │ string   │ UUID of the author PractitionerRole.           │
  │ provider.instanceroleorg         │ string   │ UUID of the custodian Organisation.            │
  │ sections                         │ dict     │ Associative array: slicename → section object. │
  │   [slicename].title              │ string   │   Section title.                               │
  │   [slicename].code               │ string   │   Pre-formatted FSH code expression.           │
  │   [slicename].display            │ string   │   Code display text.                           │
  │   [slicename].text               │ string   │   Pre-built XHTML for section.text.div.        │
  │   [slicename].indicateEmptyListReason│ string?│ "TRUE" → emptyReason instead of entries.   │
  │   [slicename].entries            │ object[] │   Array of entry objects (see above).          │
  └──────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  GLOBAL VARIABLES USED
    HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID — OID root for the Composition identifier system URI.

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    $loinc          — 60591-5 "Patient summary Document"
    $list-empty-reason — #nilknown (empty section reason)

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-02
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Composition-" ~ composition.instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: CompositionEuEps
Title: "HL7 Europe Patient Summary (EPS) Composition"
{#
  patientdisplay is set inline between FSH header lines. Twig processes the
  entire template first, so {% set %} is resolved before FSH parsing.
  patient.age is a pre-computed display string supplied by the PHP caller.
#}
{% set patientdisplay = patient.name ~ " (" ~ patient.age ~ " y/o) - synthetic data" %}
Description: "Complete HL7 Europe Patient Summary (EPS) FHIR Composition example for {{ patientdisplay }}"
Usage: #inline

{# Inject synthetic-data governance meta tags #}
{{ syntheticDataPolicyMeta() | raw }}

* id = "{{ composition.instanceid }}"

{# Composition business identifier under the HL7 Europe OID namespace #}
* identifier.system           = "urn:oid:{{ HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID }}"
* identifier.value            = "{{ composition.identifier }}"
* identifier.assigner.display = "HL7 Europe"

* title = "European Patient Summary"
* status = #final

{# Fixed LOINC type: Patient Summary Document #}
* type.coding = $loinc#60591-5 "Patient summary Document"
* type.text   = "Patient summary Document"

* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{# Author: the primary care physician's PractitionerRole #}
* author[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ provider.instancerole }})

{# Custodian: the provider's Organisation #}
* custodian[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ provider.instanceroleorg }})

{#
  Date — ISO 8601 UTC datetime format.
  The four backslashes in the format string encode two PHP-level escape
  sequences (\T → literal T, \Z → literal Z).
  Output example: 2025-09-14T12:00:00Z
#}
* date = "{{ composition.date|date('Y-m-d\\TH:i:s\\Z') }}"

* confidentiality = #N

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  SECTIONS LOOP — key-value dict iteration
  `sections` is an associative array (PHP dict): slicename → section object.
  Each section is emitted as a named FSH slice: * section[slicename]
  Named slices are always used — unnamed [+] sections are not supported here.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% set sectioncount = 0 %} {# counter for debugging; not used in FSH output #}

{% for slicename, section in sections %}

{% set sectioncount = sectioncount + 1 %}
// section, slice {{ slicename }}
//
{# Always a named slice — slicename is always the dict key #}
* section[{{ slicename }}]
  * title = "{{ section.title }}"
  * code  = {{ section.code }} "{{ section.display }}"
{# section.text is pre-built XHTML from the PHP caller; | raw prevents escaping #}
  * text.status = #generated
  * text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
{{ section.text | raw }}
</div>
"""

{#
  Empty section sentinel: when indicateEmptyListReason == "TRUE" (exact string),
  emit emptyReason and skip all entries. Mutually exclusive with the entries loop.
#}
{% if section.indicateEmptyListReason is not empty and section.indicateEmptyListReason == "TRUE" %}

  * emptyReason = $list-empty-reason#nilknown

{% else %}

{#
  ── Entries loop ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Each entry may carry an optional named slice (sectionentryslicename) and
  a suppression flag (nosectionentry). See "Entry object structure" in the
  file header.

  Entry slice assembly:
    Empty sectionentryslicename → * entry[+] = Reference(…)
    "foo"                        → * entry[foo][+] = Reference(…)
#}
{% for entry in section.entries %}

{% if entry.sectionentryslicename is empty %}
{% set sectionentryslicename = "" %}
{% else %}
{% set sectionentryslicename = "[" ~ entry.sectionentryslicename ~ "]" %}
{% endif %}

{# nosectionentry == "TRUE" suppresses the entry rule entirely #}
{% if entry.nosectionentry is empty or entry.nosectionentry != "TRUE" %}
  * entry{{ sectionentryslicename }}[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ entry.id }})
{% endif %}

{% endfor %} {# entries #}

{% endif %} {# empty reason / entries #}

{% endfor %} {# sections #}

{#
  ── Composition-level narrative — intentionally empty ────────────────────────
  Placed AFTER all sections. Each section carries its own #generated text.div;
  the Composition root text is deliberately empty.
#}
* text.status = #empty
* text.div    = "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">intentionally left empty / not meaningful</div>"

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor — intentionally empty #}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
{# HTML bag is never populated in this template; emitHTML() returns empty string #}
